                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/979: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-07T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 7, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>201. Your No. 598, December 2, 1 p.m. The War Department has, during the past
                    year, declared surplus and sold to foreign purchasers all of the artillery
                    referred to in your telegram which is fit to be used.</p>
                <p>All of the interested authorities of this Government are endeavoring to
                    facilitate in every way compatible with our own defense needs, purchases of
                    armament in this country by the Chinese Government and will endeavor to assist
                    that Government to purchase artillery here when and if the question is raised by
                    the Chinese representatives in Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
